// @test parse-errors/invalid-operator
// @description Invalid operator sequence should fail. NOTE: `1 ++ 2` is NOT invalid - TV parses it as `1 + (+2)` via unary plus (probed 2026-06-04: --tv returns no errors, x typed "const int"), and so do we. `1 ** 2` IS invalid (TV CE10156 "Syntax error at input '*'", same probe date).
// @expects parse: fail

//@version=6
indicator("Parse Error Test")

x = 1 ** 2

plot(x)
